Preheat your oven to 200°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Trim the @aubergine{1}(trimmed) then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips, then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Trim the @courgette{1}(trimmed) then slice into rounds about 1cm thick. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lemon{1/2} and cut in half.

Pop the aubergine and pepper onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the @Italian style herbs{1}(divided). Use your hands to rub the flavours all over the veg, then spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat (if you don't have one, use a normal #saucepan{} and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} later). Add the onion and fry until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, garlic and remaining Italian style herbs and cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the @risotto rice{175%g}. Cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @water{450%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{20%g}. Stir to combine. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While the risotto bakes, heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). When hot, add the courgette slices and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side. Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette picking up some nice colour. Once cooked, season with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @unsalted butter{30%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Stir through the roasted aubergine, pepper, lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season to taste with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed.

> Add a splash of water if it's a little dry.

Share the risotto between your #bowls{} and top with the charred courgettes. Cut the remaining lemon into wedges and serve alongside. Enjoy!

> STEP 3 MOD: If you've chosen to add bacon to your meal, add @?British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan before the onion. Stir-fry until golden, 4-5 mins. Add the onion to the lardons and continue as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.